<title>CSS Basic User Interface Test: cursor:text with rotated text</title>
<link rel="author" title="Florian Rivoal" href="mailto:florian@rivoal.net">
<meta name="assert" content="User agents may automatically display any angle of I-beam/cursor for text that is rendered at any particular angle">
<link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-transforms/#two-d-transform-functions">
<meta name="flags" content="interact may">
<meta charset="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-transforms/#two-d-transform-functions">
<meta name="flags" content="interact may">
<meta charset="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-transforms/#two-d-transform-functions"><meta charset="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-transforms/#two-d-transform-functions">
<meta name="flags" content="interact may">
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-ui/#cursor"><title>
</title><style>
div {
  cursor: text;
  color: blue;
  transform: rotate(45deg);
  transform-origin: bottom left;
}
p {
	cursor: text;
}
</style>
<body>
  <p>The test passes if, when moved over the blue rotated text, the cursor that indicates text that may be selected is rotated to match the angle of the text.</p><div>
  </div><p>Disregard this test if there is no rotated text.</p>
  <div>Lorem ipsum</div>
</body>
